    <text>
        <group>
            <text type="letter" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-01125">
                <body>
                    <opener>
                        <salute rend="inline">
                            <persName ref="people.xml#pan01">Никита Иванович.</persName>
                        </salute>
                    </opener>
                    <p>За приятное известие о здоровье <persName ref="people.xml#pau01"
                            >сына</persName> моего благодарствую. Я сама здорова же, и не менее его
                        печальна о неприятномъ весенном аспекте.</p>
                    <closer rend="inline">Желаю Вам здравствовать. <persName ref="people.xml#vya01"
                            >Князю Вяземскому</persName> приказала Указ заготовить по Вашему общему мнению.<lb/>
                        <signed>
                            <persName ref="people.xml#cat01">Екатерина.</persName>
                        </signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <dateline>
                            <date when-custom="1765-04-24">Апреля 24 ч., 1765.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </closer>
                </body>
            </text>
            <text type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:id="en">
                <body><opener><salute rend="inline"><persName ref="people.xml#pan01">Nikita
                                Ivanovich.</persName></salute></opener><p>Thank you for the pleasing
                        news regarding the health of my <persName ref="people.xml#pau01"
                            >son</persName>. I myself am well too, and no less saddened than he
                    by the unpleasant aspect of spring.</p><closer rend="inline">I wish you good health.
                        I have instructed <persName ref="people.xml#vya01">Prince
                            Viazemskii</persName> to prepare the decree according to your shared opinion.<lb/><signed><persName ref="people.xml#cat01"
                                >Ekaterina.</persName></signed><lb/><dateline><date
                                when-custom="1765-04-24">24 April, 1765.</date></dateline></closer>
                    </body>
            </text>
        </group>
